<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="566" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/116</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Guadalajara</hi></placeName>, [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1916-03-05T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1916-03-03T14:00:00-07:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; received March 5,
                                    1916</hi>.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s February 16, 5 p.m. Foreign Secretary says: “Sufficient
                            forces have been ordered to garrison all Cusihuiriachic region.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>